&lt;p>Eshell buffers are an option, but I am principled in my tool usage and prefer to delegate longer-running CLI tasks to a combination of Alacritty and Tmux.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Maintaining my Emacs shell usage to ephemeral popups feels natural.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Gptel&lt;sup id="fnref:2">&lt;a href="#fn:2" class="footnote-ref" role="doc-noteref">2&lt;/a>&lt;/sup> is a versatile LLM client that integrates smoothly into my workflow (buffer/text manipulation and management) without disrupting my thought flow.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>